## Summary Points

- In MLR, each coefficient is interpreted while holding all other predictors constant — always state this.
- ANCOVA includes both continuous and categorical predictors; interaction terms allow different slopes per group.
- Testing for parallel lines uses an ANOVA model comparison (F-test on the interaction term).
- Leverage measures potential influence; Cook's Distance measures actual influence.
- **High influence = high leverage AND large residual** — one alone is not sufficient.
- Cook's Distance > 1 is the standard threshold for concern.
- Cross-validation assesses generalisability of the fitted model.

